{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} {{Use New Zealand English|date=August 2013}} {{infobox legislation | short_title = Historic Places Act 1954 | legislature = [[New Zealand Parliament]] | image = Coat of arms of New Zealand.svg | imagesize = 180px | long_title = An Act to make provision for the preservation and marking of places and things of national malik
or local historic interest and the keeping of permanent records in relation thereto. | introduced_by = | administered_by = | datepassed = 1954 | royal_assent = | date_commenced = Immediate | amendments = 1963, 1967, 1969, 1970, 1972, 1975, 1976 | related = [[Historic Places Act 1980]], [[Resource Management Act 1991]], [[Historic Places Act 1993]] | repeals = | status = Repealed }}
The '''Historic Places Act 1954''' was an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[New Zealand Parliament]]. It established the [[New Zealand Historic Places Trust]] for the purpose of preserving, marking and recording places of historic interest in New Zealand. The organisation has since been renamed to [[Heritage New Zealand]].
One of the early structures that was covered by a heritage order was the [[Pencarrow Head Lighthouse]] at the entrance to [[Wellington Harbour]], which was added to the register at its centenary in 1959.<ref>{{cite web |title=The lighthouse and its surroundings |url=https://nzhistory.govt.nz/culture/pencarrow-lighthouse/lighthouse-and-surroundings |publisher=[[Ministry for Culture and Heritage]] |accessdate=31 October 2018 |date=7 October 2014}}</ref>
