{{Infobox German location | name = Mendelsheim | type = Ortsteil | Municipality = Gersheim | image_photo = | image_caption = | image_coa = Medelsheim wappen.png | coordinates = {{coord|49|08|0|N|07|12|0|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | image_plan = | plantext = | state = Saarland | district = Saarpfalz | Verbandsgemeinde = <!--none--> | Eingemeindungsdatum=1974 | elevation = 310 | area = 8.81 | population = 487 | Stand = 2000 | postal_code = 66453 | area_code = 06844 | licence = HOM | mayor = | Bürgermeistertitel= | Adresse-Verband = | Gentilic = Mendelsheimer | website = {{official website|http://www.medelsheim.de/}} }} '''Medelsheim''' is a [[Germany|German]] village, part of the municipality of [[Gersheim]], in the [[Saarpfalz-Kreis]], [[Saarland]].
== Geography == {{Empty section|date=December 2009}}
== Politics == {{Empty section|date=December 2009}}
== History == Archeological finds in Medelsheim span the period from the early Bronze Age through the Gallo-Roman period. The earliest written mention of the village of "Medilinesheim" is found in a June 28, 888 charter of the East Frankish King [[Arnulf of Carinthia|Arnulf]].
During [[World War II]] Medelsheim was briefly occupied at the beginning of the war by French troops during the September 1939 [[Saar Offensive]]. It was reoccupied by German troops the next month.
In 1995 Medelsheim was awarded a gold medal in the nationwide competition "Unser Dorf soll schöner werden" (Roughly: "Most Beautiful Village").<ref name=GG />
